-- Axa Plans $17 Million Investments in Romania This Year, ZF Says
-- B y   A n d r a   T i m u
-- 2012-06-20T05:42:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-20/axa-plans-17-million-investments-in-romania-this-year-zf-says.html
Axa SA (CS) , Europe’s second-biggest
insurer, plans to invest about 61 million lei ($17 million) in
 Romania  this year,  Ziarul Financiar  reported, citing Violeta
Ciurel, who heads the company’s Romanian unit.  Axa seeks to expand its network in the eastern European
country and plans to hire about 230 new sales consultants,
according to the Bucharest-based newspaper. The insurer
increased the capital of its Romanian unit by 9.5 million euros
($12 million) at the end of April, Ziarul Financiar said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andra Timu in Bucharest at 
 atimu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
